      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Workplaces across the UK and beyond are increasingly turning to artificial intelligence to monitor employee activity, from tracking productivity to detecting safety hazards in real time. This lesson explores how AI-powered monitoring tools work, why organisations are adopting them, and the important questions they raise around worker privacy and trust. You will look at real-world examples of how businesses are balancing the need to keep people safe with the responsibility to treat employees fairly and with respect. We will also consider the legal and ethical frameworks that guide responsible use of these technologies, including relevant UK data protection principles. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of where the line sits between legitimate safety monitoring and surveillance that goes too far.",
